NAME
    m.test - test runner from the m.icro series.

DESCRIPTION
    a test runner inspired by simplicity, written to kickstart
    the m.icro series with solid roots!

SYNOPSIS
    m.test [options] [files]

OPTIONS
    -h, --help
      outputs usage information.

    -v, --version
      outputs version number.

    -p, --parallel "maxprocs"
      run at most `maxprocs` invocations of suites at once.

    -r, --require "module"
      preload  the  specified module at startup. module may be
      either a path to a file or a node module name.
      follows `require` module resolution rules.

    -f, --filter "pattern"
      true if the last component of the pathname being examined
      matches the pattern. the match is case insensitive.

    -i, --ignore "pattern"
      false if the last component of the pathname being examined
      matches the pattern. the match is case insensitive.

    --no-ansi
      do not use ANSI escape and color codes codes.

    --debug
      enable node's debugger.

    --debug-brk
      enable node's debugger breaking on the first line.

    -w, --watch
      watches files for changes on the current cwd:
        • on Linux systems, watch uses inotify;
        • on BSD systems, watch uses kqueue;
        • on OS X, watch uses kqueue for files and FSEvents for directories;
        • on SunOS systems (including Solaris and SmartOS), watch uses event ports;
        • on Windows systems, watch feature depends on ReadDirectoryChangesW;
        • on Aix systems, watch feature depends on AHAFS, which must be enabled.

COMMANDS
    m.test-help()
      outputs usage information.

    m.test-version()
      outputs version number.

